Core Concepts

Repository (Repo) â†’ project storage (local/remote).

Commit â†’ snapshot of code (unique SHA).

Branch â†’ independent line of development.

HEAD â†’ pointer to current branch/commit.

Staging Area (Index) â†’ files prepared for commit.

Remote â†’ hosted repo (GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket).

Essential Commands

git init | clone <url>     # create or copy repo
git status                 # view changes
git add .                  # stage changes
git commit -m "message"    # commit
git push origin main       # push to remote
git pull origin main       # fetch + merge remote
git log --oneline          # history
git diff                   # show diffs


âœ… Must-know for daily DevOps work.

ğŸ”¹ 2. Medium-Level Concepts (Team Collaboration)

Branching Strategies

Feature Branching â†’ new features in isolation.

Git Flow â†’ main, develop, feature/*, release/*, hotfix/*.

Trunk-Based â†’ small, frequent merges â†’ CI/CD friendly.

Merging Approaches

Merge Commit â†’ preserves full history.

Rebase â†’ linear history, cleaner logs.

Squash Merge â†’ compress multiple commits into one.

Important Commands

git fetch                 # get latest without merge
git merge origin/main     # merge remote branch
git reset --hard <commit> # reset HEAD & working dir
git revert <commit>       # undo commit (safe)
git stash / stash apply   # save & restore temp changes
git tag v1.0.0            # version tag


GitHub Features

Pull Requests (PRs) â†’ review + merge workflow.

Issues & Projects â†’ bug tracking & Kanban.

Actions â†’ built-in CI/CD pipelines.

âœ… Enables effective collaboration.

